<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-55-0258 </DOCNO><TEXT>Computed tomography and gallium scintigraphy uncovered clinically occultmuscle infection in eight patients. The CT findings included enlargementof the muscle, effacement of the intramuscular fat planes, fluid density,rim enhancement, and involvement of the underlying bone. Computed tomographysuggested the diagnosis in seven of eight cases. Gallium scintigraphywas positive in all seven cases in which it was performed.</TEXT></DOC>